jobs_results.description:
Our client in a well-established industry is seeking a Solution Architect to be responsible for the end-to-end architecture of their enterprise systems in their digital transformation journey.

Mandatory Skill(s)
• Degree in Information Technology, Computer Engineering, Computer Science or Information System;
• Minimum 7 years of design and implementation experience with distributed applications with at least 3 years in a hands-on tech lead/system architect capacity;
• Experience in designing and developing enterprise-scale applications;
• Proficient in conceptualizing and deriving common architectural designs across multiple services;
• Good understanding of .Net/J2EE development, Service Oriented Architectures, Web Services, RESTful APIs and public websites;
• Solid Agile development experience and has experience architecting large enterprise-wide systems;
• Confident, good team player and strong stakeholder management experience;
• Interest in exploring new cutting edge... technologies;
• Strong business acumen, strategic and analytical thinking, root cause analysis, and creative problem solving ability.

Desirable Skill(s)
• TOGAF certified;
• PMP-Certified.

Responsibilities
• Provide technical expertise and establish the direction for the IT architecture, standards and design for the organisation;
• Create, evaluate and implement high-level plans and design proposals for IT solutions;
• Translate business requirements into application architectural specifications;
• Evaluate and recommend the use of leading edge technologies and methods, considering their practicality, technical limitations and criticality;
• Design the architecture blueprint of the organisation's architecture set-up using multiple models;
• Manage technical project delivery - perform code reviews and ensure performance tuning and scalability;
• Document all solution architecture design and analysis work;
• Comprehend business strategies and requirements and develop necessary designs and plans to ensure projects and solutions satisfy those needs;
• Act as a consultant to IT team and business users in the development of enterprise business architecture vision and related IT solutions to ensure that the business and IT are in alignment;
• Subject Matter Expert in addressing problems related to system and application design, performance, integration, security;
• Developing and communicating guiding principles, governance structures related to the selection of architectural components;
• Manage the technical project delivery; perform code reviews and collaborate with vendors to resolve technical challenges;
• Guide application operations, propose new solution methodologies and mentor the team raising the collective technical competencies
